                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12835039" author="yseeley@gmail.com" created="Wed, 17 Feb 2010 23:12:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The issue had to do with ords and ord normalization in sort-missing-last.&lt;br/&gt;
Here&apos;s a patch with tests and a rewritten MissingLastOrdComparator that manipulates ord values rather than trying to just handle nulls.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;note: not all tests pass yet.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12835089" author="yseeley@gmail.com" created="Thu, 18 Feb 2010 01:45:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;OK, here&apos;s the final patch with all tests passing.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12835091" author="yseeley@gmail.com" created="Thu, 18 Feb 2010 01:47:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;committed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12835424" author="hossman" created="Thu, 18 Feb 2010 21:48:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yonik: just to be verify: was this bug was introduced in Solr 1.4? ... presumably because of the changes to per segment collecting?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(that&apos;s the way the &quot;Affects Version/s&quot; is marked, but i want to sanity check in case it was actually a more fundamental problem affecting earlier versions of Solr as well).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12835451" author="yseeley@gmail.com" created="Thu, 18 Feb 2010 22:39:55 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Yonik: just to be verify: was this bug was introduced in Solr 1.4?... presumably because of the changes to per segment collecting? &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Yep.  The per-segment collecting and the FieldComparator changes caused us to rewrite all of our custom comparators... and this one had bugs.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12835936" author="lancenorskog" created="Fri, 19 Feb 2010 20:27:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Correction: Tom Hill and I have seen this bug in the distant past on Solr 1.2 or 1.3.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12835937" author="yseeley@gmail.com" created="Fri, 19 Feb 2010 20:30:17 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Correction: Tom Hill and I have seen this bug in the distant past on Solr 1.2 or 1.3. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Then it was a different bug.  This code was all new for 1.4&lt;br/&gt;
Was it reproducible, and was a bug report filed?  Can it still be reproduced?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12872805" author="hossman" created="Fri, 28 May 2010 04:15:02 +0100"  >
